                            <comment id="28641" author="david_syer" created="Fri, 21 Dec 2007 19:42:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The hibernate job blocks with high isolatio nlevels because it is reading a cursor and then updating the same objects (the cursor is in a different transaction because it uses openSession()).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The resolution is to change the isolation level - might be worth some more careful work later to encourage the right sort of best practice.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
